A ProMED-mail post

[Red tide is caused by an organism called _Gymnodinium breve_ that in high
concentration can make the water look red. The organism releases a toxin
paralyzing the respiratory system of fish and other marine life. This
particular species of _Gymnodinium_ is probably similar in that it poses a
threat to the mussel industry and to humans consuming the shellfish. - Mod.TG
